    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-14T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-14T14:00:00-05:00" n="480"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.504/1448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Ensenada</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smale</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ensenada</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-14T11:00:00-08:00"
                            >March 14, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s telegram of March 13, 5 p.m.<note n="27" xml:id="d480fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> I am reliably informed that the Governor<note n="28"
                        xml:id="d480fn2">The Governor of the Northern District of Lower
                        California.</note> returned from Mexico City with instructions of the
                    President that the constitutional rights must be respected. Nevertheless,
                    Chinese stores are to be closed and with the exception of few hours March 10th
                    have been closed solely upon the basis of alleged nonconformity with laws such
                    as reported bottom page 4 my despatch No. 797 February 28.<note n="27"
                        xml:id="d480fn3">Not printed.</note> Consulate retains conviction that the
                    Chinese are likely to be driven from business in Ensenada probably by
                    discriminatory application of minutiae of many laws and regulations which may be
                    enforced.</p>
                <p>Embassy informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smale</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
